Package logic

Class Red

java.lang.Object
logic.Red
public class Red extends Object
Represents a network (Red) with various components such as devices (equipos), connections (conexiones), locations (ubicaciones), types of cables (tiposCables), types of devices (tiposEquipos), and types of ports (tiposPuertos). Provides methods to manage these components and ensure their validity within the network.

    • modifyEquipo

      public void modifyEquipo(Equipo equipo) throws InvalidEquipoException, InvalidUbicacionException, InvalidTipoEquipoException, InvalidTipoPuertoException, InvalidDireccionIPException
      Modifies an existing device (equipo) in the network (red).

      This method first validates the modified device. If the device does not exist, an InvalidEquipoException is thrown. The old device is then removed, and the modified device is added to the map and updated in the database.

      Parameters:
      equipo - the existing device (equipo) to be replaced
      Throws:
      InvalidEquipoException - if the device does not exist
      InvalidUbicacionException - if the location (ubicacion) of the device does not exist in the network
      InvalidTipoEquipoException - if the type of device does not exist in the network
      InvalidTipoPuertoException - if one of the types of ports does not exist in the network
      InvalidDireccionIPException - if the IP address of the device is invalid

    • getEquiposIps

      public List<String> getEquiposIps()
      Retrieves the IP addresses of all devices (equipos) in the network.

      This method iterates through all devices in the network, collects their IP addresses, sorts them using a custom IP comparator, and returns the sorted list of IP addresses.

      Returns:
      a list of strings representing the sorted IP addresses of all devices in the network
